<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 01:53 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1950 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BBN-KEISSER-COLUMN-LB     05-01 0952
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-KEISSER-COLUMN-LBPT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO REASON FOR FANS TO SUPPORT ROCKER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BOB KEISSER  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ John Rocker comes to town tonight at Dodgers
Stadium, and this is not an excuse to stock up on size D batteries
and rotten fruit.
</P>
<P>
   Rocker is harmless. He is at most a sports social disease, known
around locker rooms everywhere as footus mouthus. He probably
doesn't even realize that he would be beloved in 49 states if he
had just limited his rude remarks to New York and the more unique
characteristics of its inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
   No, the most dangerous aspect of the Atlanta Braves closer, who
blasted a potpourri of humanity in a December issue of Sports
Illustrated, are those in orbit around him.
</P>
<P>
   An altogether too large group of fans, in Atlanta but also in
San Diego this past weekend, have cheered Rocker and sought his
autograph, as if there was something honorable in what he said and
the way he said it, as if there were some truths between the lines.
</P>
<P>
   There is no valid reason for anyone to seek Rocker out and
support him. Even if you believe he has the right to say anything
he wants, that he should be afforded the same freedom of speech as
everyone else regardless of how rude or moronic he may be, he
shouldn't be turned into some kind of sage of the politically
incorrect.
</P>
<P>
   Deeply loyal Braves fans, who drone on endlessly with the
equally P.I. Tomahawk Chop, can be excused because they would
support anyone in a Braves uniform if he could help them win a
World Series. If Elian Gonzalez was 18 and had a splitter, he would
have been adopted by Ted Turner before papa even knew he was gone.
</P>
<P>
   But this drift of opinion appears to go beyond Braves fans. The
mot-so-silent majority lining up behind him Rocker are making their
own statement, and it's even more distasteful than Rockers'.
</P>
<P>
   It's just more proof that our species isn't fully evolved. Maybe
some people read or heard only the short version, that he took
shots at different races and gays. Some people are plumb tired of
incidents like this -- Fuzzy Zoeller on Tiger Woods, Reggie White
on a similar cross-section of mankind -- and irked at the messenger
as a result. And admittedly, the media has developed some bad
habits.
</P>
<P>
   But that shouldn't color anyone's opinion of Rocker. His words
speak for themselves. For those who have forgotten:
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Imagine having to take the seven train (in New York) to the
ballpark, looking like Beirut, looking at some kid with purple hair
next to some queer with AIDS right next to some dude who just got
out of jail for the fourth time right next to some 20-year-old mom
with four kids. It's depressing.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``I'm not a very big fan of foreigners. You can walk an entire
block in Times Square and not hear anybody speaking English. Asians
and Koreans and Vietnamese and Indians and Russians and Spanish
people ... How the hell did they get in this country?''
</P>
<P>
   _ About a female driver, he said ``Stupid b----! Learn to
f---ing drive!'' When another female driver strayed into his lane,
he said ``Look at this idiot. I guarantee you she's a Japanese
woman.''
</P>
<P>
   Oh, and he also called a black teammate a fat monkey'' and said
the Braves lost a game because shortstop Walt Weiss was too old.
And during the postseason against the Mets and Yankees, he spit at
fans, gave them the finger, and threw a 90-mph ball at a net fence
separating the fans from the field.
</P>
<P>
   By all means, let's cheer the man and invite him over for a
barbeque.
</P>
<P>
   What strikes me most about Rocker is that he's dumb.
</P>
<P>
   He volunteered everything he said. This wasn't a case of a
writer (Jeff Pearlman wrote the SI article) provoking someone to
speak, using quotes that were off-the-record, or playing
buddy-buddy with a guy and then turning on him. Rocker knew his New
York experience was on top of the agenda. And still he went off on
a rant.
</P>
<P>
   In his rushed apologies, Rocker said he wasn't racist or
prejudiced, and that he was baited by New York fans. But it is now
de rigeur for athletes who say racist things to say they're not
racist, as if we're supposed to draw a distinction when they use
the buzzwords.
</P>
<P>
   If he had any smarts, he could have just couched his words like
a Pat Buchanan or Rush Limbaugh.
</P>
<P>
   Oh, what a shame it is that so many large American cities have
blighted communities, he could have said. Or he could have lamented
that family values have deteriorated to the point where kids act
out, where there are too many young, single mothers, and that many
of their fathers are in and out of the penal system.
</P>
<P>
   See John? The difference between a bigot and a conservative
politician is merely a vocabulary.
</P>
<P>
   And timing. With so many people apparently in favor of sending
Elian home to Cuba, perhaps John's thoughts about immigration
simply were ahead of their time. I tried to ask the Dodgers Devon
White about the positive responses to Rocker, and he pondered the
question for a moment before politely declining to get in the
middle of it.
</P>
<P>
   If only Rocker would have had the same common sense when that
reporter came to Macon. No SI article, no penalty from Major League
Baseball, no headlines, no zippy one-liners from sports columnists
and talk show hosts. Just a dysfunctional relationship with a
dysfunctional city, New York.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, John Rocker comes to town in assorted regalia -- Braves
closer, insensitive idiot, knee-jerk reactionary hero, symbol for
all that ails sports and its fans. I close with one of his quotes
from the SI article: I'm not a racist or prejudiced person. But
certain people bother me.''
</P>
<P>
   Yeah, like John Rocker and his fans.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-01-00 0153EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000501.0034 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-01 01:55 </DATE_TIME>
