<SLUG> BC-CAR-NAPA-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NASCAR: 10 RACES, 10 WINNERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By STEVE RAMIREZ  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   FONTANA - Sunday's NAPA Auto Parts 500 produced the 10th
different winner in NASCAR Winston Cup this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's unbelievable,'' three-time Winston Cup champion Jeff
Gordon said. ``It's pretty amazing how competitive it is right now.
Any guy can win. It's just hitting the right combination.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Winner Jeremy Mayfield) was fast all day, and he deserved to
win (Sunday). I've never seen it like this. It's good for the
sport, but it makes it tougher to get up to the front and battle
for wins.''
</P>
<P>
   Worst finish: Gordon's recent dominance of California Speedway
ended with an 11th-place finish.
</P>
<P>
   It was his worse finish in four races here. He won in 1997 and
'99 and finished fourth two years ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a tricky racetrack,'' said Gordon, who started 26th and
was running seventh early on. ``The groove really widened out, and
you just never knew where you could run. It was really good for us
at the beginning. We moved up through the field. We just used up
our tires coming to the front.
</P>
<P>
   ``Eleventh is not bad. We'd have liked a top 10, but we're doing
what we need to stay in the top 10 in points. I think maybe we lost
one or two positions (Sunday), but we'll go get 'em at Richmond
(Va.).''
</P>
<P>
   Disappointments: Sunday was another long day for former CART
driver Scott Pruett and former Winston Cup champion Darrell
Waltrip.
</P>
<P>
   Pruett, who hadn't placed higher than 19th in the previous nine
races, finished a disappointing 34th. He started sixth but quickly
dropped to 30th by lap 10 and 41st after 30 laps.
</P>
<P>
   Waltrip, who is retiring at the end of the season, finished
29th.
</P>
<P>
   ``Most of the day we were loose,'' said Waltrip, who started
seventh. ``Loose, loose, loose. We did run well on one set of
tires, but another set really cost us.
</P>
<P>
   ``Maybe we're trying some things we shouldn't be trying. I don't
know. Our qualifying run and the reaction (Sunday) from the fans
still made my last race (at California Speedway) memorable.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-01-00 0212EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
