 UNDATED: ... the problem.  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   On April 21, however, the company sent out an e-mail to about
5,500 customers warning them that a billing error had occurred that
might result in incorrect charges to their credit or debit cards.
The company said it would immediately credit any charges billed to
the customers' accounts, whether correct or incorrect, and issue
revised statements.
</P>
<P>
   Essential.com is preparing to sell stock to the public. In a
recent filing, it acknowledged its customer service struggles.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have recently experienced a period of rapid growth that has
strained, and may continue to strain, our customer service,
financial, operational, marketing, and management systems and
resources,'' the filing said. ``Our anticipated growth, as well as
the requirements we will face as a public company, will place
additional burdens on our resources.''
</P>
