<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    No time for gym?
 &HT;    by Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   The Georgia Board of Education is trying to decide how much time
students in kindergarten through eighth grade will spend running,
throwing and doing push-ups at school next year.
</P>
<P>
   Physical education no longer is required by state law for
kindergarten through eighth grade. Gov. Roy Barnes, who proposed
the change in the law, wants kids to focus on core subjects, such
as science and math.
</P>
<P>
   Even though the law doesn't require PE, the state Board of
Education still can make schools hold the classes. The board is
holding meetings on the issue.
</P>
<P>
   Some people are upset by the new law because they don't feel
kids are active enough. Others say parents should make sure their
kids exercise.
</P>
<P>
   What is your opinion? Write us at nfk(at)ajc.com!
</P>
<P>
   LOCUSTS ATTACK AUSTRALIA
</P>
<P>
   About 100 billion locusts are on the move through Australia's
outback. The winged insects already have attacked crops in South
Australia and are headed for richer agricultural areas.
</P>
<P>
   Officials estimate the vermin could cause $150 million in
damage.
</P>
<P>
   The plague is described as the worst in 20 years.
</P>
<P>
   Record rainfalls have created damp soil, which the locusts need
to hatch eggs. The extra rain also has increased plant life the
locusts feed on.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're spraying what we find,'' said plague manager Walter
Spratt. ``We're trying to do as much as we can
</P>
<P>
   as fast as we can.''
</P>
<P>
   WHEW! THRILL-RIDE PRICES RISE
</P>
<P>
   The price of experiencing death-defying dips on roller coasters
has risen this year. The average adult admission price in North
America is $2.70 higher than last season's price, making the
average adult ticket $37. That's the largest increase in seven
years, according to a survey of 30 theme parks conducted by an
industry magazine.
</P>
<P>
   Recently, Disneyland in California began applying its adult
price of $41 to visitors 10 and older. The price previously started
at age 12. Disney World in Florida raised its adult price by $1, to
$46 per ticket.
</P>
<P>
   Park officials say the increases reflect better rides.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
