r k BC-COMMENTARY-BJT02-COX     05-01 0653
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT02-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Tuesday, May 2, 2000 are moving today
to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   HALL-IRAQ-COMMENTARY _ DAYTON, Ohio _ ``You will look evil in
the eye if you go to Iraq,'' an American aid worker warned before I
visited the country. I spotted it immediately. It was ubiquitous in
the fear that seems to haunt Iraqis' eyes, and in the pain of
starvation and disease that plagues so many of them. It was clear
in the countless military fortifications along every road, evidence
of its wars with its neighbors, and in the terrible persecution of
minorities in its northern and southern regions. (U.S. Rep. Tony P.
Hall for Cox News Service). MOVED FRIDAY.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ My wife is hosting a garden party. I'm
hosting a dog party. For most of the morning, members of my wife's
garden club will be gathered in our back yard, sipping coffee or
tea and nibbling on sandwiches hardly the size of piano keys. I'll
be with my dogs, in the little house that's way in the back yard.
If I sound bitter, it's for good reason. I'm good and bitter about
a party at my house that I'm not invited to, not to mention my
eight dogs. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED FRIDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ It's that time of year when
a man's fancy turns to _ morels. At least that's the way it goes
here in our village. Not that the other thing they're supposed to
be hankering for in the spring doesn't matter. It does, but for a
couple of weeks at least, it comes limping in a poor second because
the only thing on these men's minds right now is MUSHROOMS.
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ My social isolation is about to become complete. I
no longer spend much time at the gas station standing in line
behind the lottery players and listening to the guys around the
coffee pot. I pay at the pump, pump my own and am out in two
minutes. I don't go to the post office very often. Almost all my
correspondence is in the form of e-mail and some of my bills are
now automatically deducted from my bank account.(Lane, Daytona
Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTOS, LAYOUTS and GRAPHICS CoxNet layouts are for sale over
the web, through the New York Times News Service's PageExpress
service, at http://nytsyn.com/syndicate/pageex.
</P>
<P>
   If a budget line or story is marked with photos or graphics,
those are available from the New York Times News Service at
212-556-4204. Or call CoxNet for more information at 404-526-5456.
</P>
