   CATS-BIRDS (Undated) _ A major observance for American bird
lovers is just around the corner: National Keep Your Cat Indoors
Day. The cat lobby supports the May 13 event in principle, but is
somewhat ambivalent: It conveys a negative image of Fluffy as the
murderer of Tweety Bird, they say. National Keep Your Cat Indoors
Day is the brainchild of the American Bird Conservancy. By ERIC
BRAZIL.
</P>
<P>
