   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-4-DOOR-PICKUPS (Undated) _ Nissan introduced the Frontier
Crew-Cab in January 1999, and the truck went on sale in late spring
'99 as a 2000 model. It was the first compact pickup to offer a
real bench seat in the rear, with normal-size doors for the
rear-seat passengers to use _ one on each side of the vehicle. But
no sooner had Nissan rolled out the Frontier Crew-Cab than
DaimlerChrysler introduced the Dakota. By G. CHAMBERS WILLIAMS III.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-NISSAN-XTERRA (Undated) _ Good luck finding one. And if you
can, and the dealer isn't adding several thousand dollars to the
sticker as some California dealers have, then you might find that
the all-new Nissan Xterra sport-utility vehicle is a real bargain.
By G. CHAMBERS WILLIMAS III.
</P>
