<P>
   &UR; ELIAN GONZALEZ: MOVED, BUT STILL A PAWN &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ELIAN-SAGA-LIMBO-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MIAMI _ A screaming boy, policemen pointing guns,
Cuban-Americans burning flags. The Elian Gonzalez affair reached a
new crescendo with the armed removal of the six-year-old from the
home of his Miami relatives. So, now that Elian has been reunited
with his father in Maryland, you might expect a speedy conclusion
to the affair, right? Don't count on it. With Cuban exiles still
smarting from a mixture of tear gas, pepper spray and public
humiliation, lawyers for the boy's Miami relatives are already
planning to erect new legal obstacles. &QL;
</P>
