   &UR; THE AMERICAS &LR;  &QC;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MEXICO'S PRESIDENTIAL RACE GETS `MUY CALIENTE' AFTER ALL &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PRI-NO-SHOO-IN-MEXICO-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY _ The vote is not until July 2, but as the campaign
for Mexico's presidential election got under way in earnest this
week, two things confirmed that it will not be like any other in
the country's history. What once looked like a walkover for the
ruling PRI party, which has held power since the 1920s, has turned
into a hotly contested fight after all. &QL;
</P>
