   (975 words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MOREOVER &LR;  &QC;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THOUSANDS OF ANTIQUITIES DOOMED BY TURKISH DAM. DOES ANYONE
CARE? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DAM-SHAME-TURKEY-ECONOMIST-575&AMP;add &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GAZIANTEP, TURKEY _ Countless archaeological treasures _
irreplaceable treasures _ will be buried under the waters of the
Euphrates River when the newly completed Birecik Dam starts filling
up on April 29. ``We are about to witness a great tragedy,'' says a
distressed Dr. Catherine Abadie Reynal, a French archaeologist who
has been digging there since 1996. ``A second Ephesus is about to
be lost. And no one seems to have lifted a finger to stop it.'' &QL;
</P>
