<HEADLINE>
`BEING JOHN MALKOVICH': CURIOUSER AND CURIOUSER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Being John Malkovich'' _ Movie art is
momentarily rescued from the marketers with this wacky,
idiosyncratic, ingenious comedy with John Cusack and, yes, John
Malkovich. Think ``Alice in Wonderland,'' an amusement park on
psychedelic drugs, tall people, low ceilings, and a whole lot of
inventive fun. If you liked ``Brazil,'' you'll love this one.
</P>
<P>
   ``Galaxy Quest'' _ This hilarious parody of a ``Star Trek''-type
cast was a surprise hit last year. It's better on the DVD, which
includes an entire track in the alien's language.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Image Entertainment, the company that supported the ill-fated
laserdisc format, is riding the DVD market to expansion and
profitability. President Martin Greenwald has signed an agreement
with Black Entertainment Television to coproduce a series of jazz
concerts to be cablecast on BET. Image will retain home video
rights. Citing a strong growth in DVD sales, Image saw its income
grow by more than 10 percent in the last quarter.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DVD PICK OF THE WEEK: Sydney Pollack's ``Out of Africa,'' which
starred Meryl Streep and Robert Redford and won seven Oscars in
1985, including best picture, gets the full DVD treatment. It has a
widescreen format and a 50-minute documentary on Karen Blixen, the
Danish author whose memoirs were the basis for the film, and an
informative commentary by the director. Pollack, talking his way
through the romantic drama on a separate audio track, gives full
credit to Streep and Redford for the film's success. How rare _ a
director willing to share the credit.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 9: ``American Beauty,'' ``The Hollywood
Knights,'' ``Bringing Out the Dead.'' May 16: ``The World Is Not
Enough'' (DVD), ``Dreaming of Joseph Lees,'' ``Felicia's Journey,''
``The End of the Affair.'' May 23: ``Sleepy Hollow,'' ``Escape From
Mars,'' ``Train of Life.'' May 30: ``Snow Falling on Cedars''
(DVD), ``Miss Julie,'' ``Man on the Moon'' (DVD).'' June 6: ``Girl,
Interrupted'' (DVD), ``Mr. Death'' (DVD), ``Backlash,'' ``Kiss the
Sky'' (DVD), ``A Scandal in Paris,'' ``On Our Merry Way'' (DVD),
``Andy Kaufman Plays Carnegie Hall.''
</P>
</TEXT>
