<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    With SENIORS-HOUSING.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PREPARING A HOME FOR ELDERLY LIVING
</P>
<P>
   The five major modifications made by those 45 and older who are
permitted to alter their residences:
</P>
<P>
   _ Light switch at stairwell, 24 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ Handrails or grab bars in bath, 18 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ Handrails on both sides of stairwell, 17 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ Changes to live on first floor, 14 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ Widened doorways, 9 percent
</P>
<P>
   The five simple modifications made by those 45 and older who are
permitted to alter their residences:
</P>
<P>
   _ Night lights, 60 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ Non-skid bathtub strips, 44 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ High-wattage light bulbs, 31 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ Larger numbers on telephone, 21 percent
</P>
<P>
   _ Levers to replace faucet knobs, 19 percent
</P>
<P>
   Source: AARP National Survey of Housing and Home Modification
Issues.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
