<HEADLINE>
HOT TRAVEL DEALS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sun., May 7)  
 By JANET PIORKO    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   B&AMP;B THE FRENCH WAY _ A six-night package in France offered by
Country Cottages of Boca Raton, Fla., starts at $1,098 a person,
double occupancy, through June 15, including bed-and-breakfast
lodgings, round-trip trans-Atlantic air fare and a rental car. The
package, called ``Go As You Please _ Decouvrir la France,'' offers
a choice of 500 places to stay throughout the country; all have
rooms with private bath. Travelers receive vouchers for their rooms
and can reserve their first night before departure; the rest are
booked as they go, with a free phone call from each night's
lodging. (Alternatively, Country Cottages will make the
reservations for $12 per location.) The price of $1,098 is also
good from Sept. 16 through Oct. 31. From June 16 to Sept. 15 and
Dec. 16 to 24, it is $1,296, dropping to $899 from November to
mid-December and January through March. Flights are on British
Airways via London. The car is a stick-shift economy model with
unlimited mileage. Reservations: (800) 674-8883.
</P>
<P>
   SAILING THE MEDITERRANEAN _ First European Cruises is offering
savings averaging $1,000 a person on September and October voyages
of the 1,200-passenger Mistral in the eastern Mediterranean. The
ship, which entered service in July, sails round trip from Venice
on Saturdays from June through October on seven-day cruises to
Dubrovnik, Katakolon (for Olympia), Santorini, Mykonos, Rhodes and
Piraeus (for Athens). The special rates start at $949 a person, for
double occupancy in an inside cabin; from $1,110 for an outside
cabin; the rate is $1,800 a person for a mini-suite with balcony.
Round-trip flights to and from Venice are priced at $950 from the
East Coast. The ship's management aims to carry a mix of Europeans
and about 15 percent North Americans; the international dining-room
staff and stewards are English speaking. There are two outdoor
pools, a spa and thalassotherapy center. Information: (888)
983-8767 or www.first-european.com.
</P>
<P>
   EL AL COMPANION FARES _ Through Dec. 31, passengers in first and
business class flying round trip between the United States and
Israel on El Al can buy a companion ticket in the same class for
$250. From New York to Tel Aviv, the summer first-class fare is
$7,754, business class $5,258. The companion tickets must be
purchased directly from El Al. For more information: (212)
768-9200.
</P>
<P>
   TOUR OF THAILAND _ Grand Circle Travel, geared to those 50 and
over, has a Jewels of Thailand itinerary from October through early
May 2001 that starts at $1,195 a person, double occupancy,
including air fare from New York and 16 other cities, six nights'
lodging in Bangkok and seven in Chiang Mai, and many meals. (The
lowest price is for late April and early May, going up to $1,445 in
October.) For more information: (800) 248-3737.
</P>
