<P>
   KENT-CUSELLA _ On the evening of May 4, 1970, as other Kent
State University students were hurriedly packing their belongings
and heading for home, Lou Cusella was alone in the basement of the
a morgue, waiting to identify the body of his friend and roommate
William Schroeder. Three of the students killed on the campus that
earlier in the day by Ohio National Guardsmen _ Sandra Scheuer,
Allison Krause and Jeffrey Miller _ had already been identified.
The body of the fourth victim lay on a gurney in the room next door
to where Cusella was sitting. (Batz, Dayton Daily News) WITH
PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
