<SLUG> BC-LODGIANQCOX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Lodgian suffers loss, but outlook remains positive
 &HT;    By Shelia M. Poole
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Atlanta-based Lodgian Inc. Monday reported a fourth-quarter loss
of $66.5 million, or $2.39 a share, before extraordinary items.
</P>
<P>
   Revenue was $140.7 million for the quarter and $592.4 million
for the year.
</P>
<P>
   The results were delayed twice because of the integration of
multiple accounting systems following the 1998 merger of Servico
and Impac, which created Lodgian.
</P>
<P>
   Chief Executive Robert Cole said cash flow was in line with
management's expectations and that he expected the year to be
positive.
</P>
<P>
   But some analysts are taking a wait-and-see attitude.
</P>
<P>
   ``The most telling number in the fourth quarter is that RevPar
(revenue per available room) was flat for the stabilized
properties,'' said Paul Puryear, an analyst with Raymond James in
St. Petersburg, Fla. ``Obviously the conclusion is not rocket
science. This was not a very good quarter with the level of
write-offs they had and the flat number in same-store stabilized
properties.''
</P>
<P>
   Puryear said the lodging industry is ``looking a little better,
probably for the first time in a year and a half. Based on the
current trend, I think Lodgian's asset value should be on the
uptick for the rest of the year.''
</P>
<P>
   The company has hired an investment banker to review strategic
alternatives, including a possible sale.
</P>
<P>
   ``Nothing is being ruled out at this point,'' said Cole
</P>
<P>
   Kentucky businessman William Yung Sr. made a bid for the company
last year. Yung said he is still interested in acquiring the
company and has filed a lawsuit in Delaware seeking to overturn a
decision by Lodgian to reduce the number of board members.
</P>
<P>
   The company is also selling properties to reduce $880 million in
debt. Sixteen hotels have been sold since the beginning of 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Lodgian (LOD)
</P>
<P>
   4th quarter ended Dec. 31
</P>
