the Texas-Mexico border are threatening to stop handling small-time
drug cases referred by federal officials unless Washington starts
compensating them. District attorneys in Cameron, Hidalgo, and El
Paso counties say they are being overwhelmed by cases passed on by
federal prosecutors. By JAMES PINKERTON.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-EXECUTION (Houston) _ The U.S. Supreme Court clears the
way for the execution of convicted killer Gary Graham. Graham,
backed by opponents of the death penalty and black activists,
contends that he is innocent and his lawyers say they will not be
dissuaded by the high court's action. By STEVE BREWER and LISA
TEACHEY.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-BONFIRE (Undated) _ Texas A&AMP;M gears up for Tuesday's
report to the special commission investigating last year's deadly
bonfire. The Nov. 12 accident killed 12 people and injured 27
others. By JOHN WILLIAMS.
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER-ASSAULT (Houston) _ Oscar Peralta remains under detention
by the Immigration and Naturalization Service even though a
mistrial was declared in an assault case stemming from a
confrontation at a high school soccer game. By EDWARD HEGSTROM.
</P>
