   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Vice President Al Gore points out
correctly that Gov. George W. Bush lacks experience in foreign
policy, compared to Gore's own extensive knowledge. But so what?
History shows that prior experience has very little to do with how
well presidents handle international affairs. By MARIANNE MEANS.
(Already filed.)
