Archeologist David Starbuck with earthenware beer bottles, circa
1900, unearthed at the Shaker Village in Canterbury, N.H.
Starbuck's discoveries suggest that, counter to the ascetic image
popularized by 20th-century historians, ``quite a lot of alcohol''
was being consumed in the village. (Tom Herde/The Boston Globe)
