<P>
   BC-SENATE-AMBASSADORS-NYT (moved on Thursday, April 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, April
27, about a request by two major Foreign Service organizations for
the Senate to end the blocking of two ambassadorial appointments
misattributed the action. It was taken by Senator Charles Grassley,
Republican of Iowa, acting independently, and not by the Senate
Foreign Relations Committee.
</P>
<P>
   BC-NY-GIULIANI-CANCER-NYT (moved on Thursday, April 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, April
27, about Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani's announcement that he has
prostate cancer referred incorrectly to his standing in upstate New
York opinion polls. A recent New York Times/CBS News poll found
Giuliani, among upstate voters, even with Hillary Rodham Clinton,
his opponent for the United States Senate. In other polls, the
mayor is running ahead of Clinton upstate. He is not running behind
her there.
